OL,6,FDetective Sergeant Carla Dalton, from
OL,7,FGMP's City of Manchester prison team,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Every single phone we remove
OL,9,Ffrom a prison cell is a blow to
OL,10,Forganised crime.
OL,12,F"These devices are not harmless - they
OL,13,Fare used to arrange drug deals, weapon
OL,14,Fdrops and even plan violent attacks.
OL,16,F"By seizing and destroying these
OL,17,Felectronic devices, we are cutting off
OL,18,Fthe line that offenders rely on to
OL,19,Fcontinue their criminality from behind
OL,20,Fbars.
