OL,6,F"This work is about protecting the
OL,7,Fpublic and ensuring that those serving
OL,8,Fsentences cannot exploit technology to
OL,9,Fharm our communities any further."
OL,11,FHaving an electronic device in prison
OL,12,Fis an offence under the Prison Act
OL,13,F1952 and the Criminal Justice and
OL,14,FPublic Order Act 1994.
OL,16,FAny prisoner found guilty of
OL,17,Fpossessing a device could face
OL,18,Fadditional jail time.
